To simplify \(\displaystyle \frac{-\tfrac{8}{7}}{4}\), rewrite the division as multiplication by the reciprocal of 4:

\[
\frac{-\tfrac{8}{7}}{4}
= -\frac{8}{7}\;\times\;\frac{1}{4}
= -\frac{8}{28}
= -\frac{2}{7}.
\]

To simplify \(-\frac{3}{\tfrac{9}{10}}\), multiply by the reciprocal of \(\tfrac{9}{10}\):

\[
-\frac{3}{\tfrac{9}{10}}
= -3\;\times\;\frac{10}{9}
= -\frac{30}{9}
= -\frac{10}{3}.
\]
